Author:
Vol / Page: 4 : 2
Edition:
Quote: Within the country, New Zealand was after 1840 known as <i>the Colony</i>, and subsequently as <i>the Dominion</i>, the title it carried from 1907 until the 1940s or somewhat later. Now it is simply <i>the country</i>, or more formally <i>the nation</i>, and of course <i>home</i> (as opposed to <i>Home</i>) for those Kiwis who are temporarily absent from it.
